<bioghist altrender="history" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
<head>Historical Note</head>
<p>
The town of Wilton was incorporated in May 1802 and was taken from Norwalk. The town is located in Fairfield County.
</p>
</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
<head>Scope and Content</head>
<p>
Military discharge papers, 1942, 1944-1947, 1949, 1952-1956, 1958-1961, 1966; Voter registration applications, 1944-1946, 1948, 1950, 1952, 1954, 1957-1960, 1963-1970, 1972.
These application forms are called "Application by Member of the Armed Forces of the United States for Absentee Admission as an Elector" through January 1966. After that the 
forms are called "Application for Absentee Admission as an Elector".
</p>
</scopecontent>

<arrangement encodinganalog="351$b" id="a5">
<head>Arrangement</head>
<p>
The militrary discharge papers are arranged alphabetically by last name. The voter registration applications are arranged chronologically by approval/denial date.
</p>
</arrangement>

<relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1" id="a6">
<head>Related Material</head>
<p>None.</p>
</relatedmaterial>



